Officer, Court of the Crosswinds <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uavalisschadenfreude.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Avalis Schadenfreude</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/18/01 12:24:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=921.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Change?</span><hr size=1> FACES - option to change our hair styles and colours every so often... maybe every 10 levels or something so that it reflects the changes and aging of our characters.  I want to have a grey hair when I reach 60, but I don't really want it right now as lowly 13th.<br>
<br>
A. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/18/01 1:00:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=921.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Here's my take on it:</span><hr size=1> TLC -- out. Put it back if server ever gets crowded enough that farmers are a problem. At a minimum, all quest items and all trade-skill items must be obtainable at any level.<br>
<br>
Alignment -- let anyone group with anyone if neutral invites; ie. bless the bug (if it is a bug). Same with guilding. It is just plain pointless to have good&amp;evil if they can't interact directly. That's the fun of it. Good/good and evil/evil is boring. Keep the buffing restrictions.<br>
<br>
Alignment change -- not with a /command. Force people that want to change to go into a city of predominately that alignment and talk to an NPC there to obtain a change; ie. you have to really live the alignment to change it. If you want to put the work in, you should be able to become just about any alignment you want.<br>
<br>
Remove the forced /roleplay. It's a nice thought, but it makes it terribly hard to build groups; eg. need to find a cleric, which clerics are on now? You can only ask the ones that spring to mind by name. Grouping should be promoted in all ways and this inhibits grouping. If you don't see the problem now, you will see it when you reach 40+ and by 50+, it will be a severe hardship.<br>
<br>
Languages -- I like the changes a lot, but I'd have capped them at 10*level, not 5*(level+1). Level 10 or so is when people start doing a lot of traveling and meeting new people. The language issue is a nice touch, but it's a bit too much of a barrier as is. Socializing is good and should be promoted.<br>
<br>
Languages part II -- NPCs should only speak their native tongue, not &quot;universal&quot;. This provides another incentive to learn languages other than &quot;I can't talk to anyone&quot;. Same thing for quest notes and other written materiels. Native tongue (this one should go into all servers, not just FV).<br>
<br>
Languages, the revenge -- NPC vendors should only work as they do now if you have mastered the language.  If you haven't, they should increase sale prices and decrease buy prices.  This would be another incentive other than a need to communicate with other PCs (pc-to-pc talk really should be a pretty basic ability).<br>
<br>
Auction -- I'm of two minds here. With the huge down-times associated with solo'ing, /auc in every zone gives you something to do and also gives a much better chance of finding the merchant or buyer you need. 'Course, if you can setup a group, you won't have time for this nonsense. Maybe if this board was more popular, the trade sections here will eventually cover it (or if /vendorme goes live).<br>
<br>
High-elf guards -- make some low-level pinkies for the darks to hunt in Faydwer. The dark races should be encouraged to attack and kill good race NPCs in just about every good NPC city or outpost. After all, they're evil. They should not only be able to go out and be evil, they should be rewarded in game for it. Good race folk should have extremely severe penalties for attacking other good race NPCs.<br>
<br>
Evil quests -- slaving!  Evils should have a way to take prisoners back and sell them.  The game badly needs some good/evil interaction where each side is encouraged to do things appropriate for their alignment.<br>
<br>
Good quests -- slaving part II.  Goods should have a way to rescue slaves (both combat/raid and stealth style).  PC slaves might be going a bit too far, but NPC would be quite fun for both sides. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ustormtower.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormtower</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Travelling Circus</span><br>  Posts: 280<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/18/01 1:44:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=921.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Here's my take on it:</span><hr size=1> I like Bjond's ideas on languages.  It does kind of bother me that all the NPCs speak &quot;universal&quot;.  I'd like Orcs to speak in orc, Goblins to speak in goblin, etc.<br>
<br>
(as a side note, I was hunting hoppers in Luclin, and one of them actually said the &quot;Halfelves like you ruined your lands, you'll not ruin mine!&quot; ... got me thinking ... Hoppers can talk???)<br>
<br>
<br>
Re:  Good vs. Evil<br>
<br>
Yeah ... we do need to see some type of storyline developing that is NOT GM-run.  Instead of the day-in and day-out frozen status that it is now, we should see the Commonlands getting overrun by the dark elves now and then ... and then next week, see a small squadron of good guards guarding the area from the commonlands to the bridge when the Freeporters battle back.<br>
<br>
Or, how about: with the opening of the Luclin portals, we'll see an invasion army taking over entire zones starting from the portals.  It would be interesting to see if the Iksar are actually ambitious enough to rush into ShadowHaven and take over Feydwer from two fronts -- the ocean and the portal.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxsatyrx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xsatyrx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/18/01 1:45:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=921.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Here's my take on it:</span><hr size=1> &quot;As Seen recently, a DE has forsaken Innoruk in our world. Now many may not aggree with her role-play choices, but it is not their character. I commend her for trying though and think it should be allowed. Now i know that many of you disagree with me but i think slight changes in alignment should be allowed for any race to almost any alignment. <br>
how would we keep the balance? when a person makes a drastic alignment change, like DE to a neutral alignment, they become KOS to their respective race instantaineously and there they stand and must improve from there. if as drastic as evil to good, they become KOS to ALL evil races. The good still hate them also, so very careful work must be done to increase their faction. now i do not think that a Cleric or Druid should be allowed to cross their god for that would destroy their character's ability to perform their abilities being they come from 'their god' as i see it in role-play. If this could be allowed, then converting would be possible and full role-play possibilies would exist. Now what would stop all from doing this kind of change? Making good from KOS is a VERY tedious thing as i see it seems every town is split into 3 or more factions. For example, lets say this DE went to Crushbone to raise faction...killing orcs helps with guards...not the merchants. So i do think it should be possible as long as the class considered does not need to worship a god to function. This probably is only my dream because im sure the coding involved would probably be too much for the benefits given as Verant would see it. I am curious to see all of your opinions on this idea though. &quot;<br>
<br>
This is what i posted on another board....i would love to see what others think...<br>
<br>
Dhugal<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ustormtower.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormtower</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Travelling Circus</span><br>  Posts: 283<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/18/01 3:08:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=921.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Here's my take on it:</span><hr size=1> <br>
Dhugal -- yeah, I'd like to see people changing religions and not just their alignment.  Currently, we're stuck in a &quot;your religion and class determines the flexibility of your alignment&quot;.  Real roleplaying would lead to very mutable characters.<br>
<br>
Of course, we'll have to take consequences of changes in religion.  Going from Mithaniel Marr to Erollisi Marr should not have too many repurcussions ... but Innothule to Erollisi?  Ouch ... Innothule should be hunting you down the way Hera (Greek goddess) punished anyone who defied her.<br>
<br>
To support that idea, I'd suggest &quot;missionary&quot; NPCs for various religions (maybe in the Bazaar) where you can undergo a quest.  Finish the quest, and you can change religions.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Another thought along the same lines, but this is probably impossible:  How about &quot;multiclassing&quot;.  A character starts life as a street rat (rogue), using his hide, sneak, and &quot;critical hits from the back side&quot; to survive ... he eventually earns a living as a scout and learns how to survive in the wilderness (ranger) ... a period of war comes along and he is drafted into the army (warrior).<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxsatyrx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xsatyrx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/18/01 4:15:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=921.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Here's my take on it:</span><hr size=1> wonderful idea storm, but i bet its even more impossible than my idea)<br>
<br>
Dhugal<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ustormtower.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormtower</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Travelling Circus</span><br>  Posts: 285<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/18/01 4:32:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=921.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Here's my take on it:</span><hr size=1> yeah... it's a side effect of playing too much 3rd Edition D&amp;D.  I happen to play a lot of multiclassed melee characters.  I'm currently working on figuring out a combo that maximizes AC and Saving Throws.  There's a couple of prestige classes that work well ...<br>
<br>
*shudder*  Ok ... back to EQ. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugrimwyrd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimwyrd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/18/01 6:28:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=921.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Here's my take on it:</span><hr size=1> I personally like all the limitations on this server, and would even add more =)<br>
<br>
For instance if it wasn't for the obvious problems with LD, I'd like to see the /invite command only work in cities. Yes, I realize this is shocking and nasty, with many problems. But I like the thought of forcing people to meet in cities and form groups. An exception could be that guildmates can be invited to your group in any zone.<br>
<br>
Basically any further restrictions that forced people to socialize and come together would be fun for me.<br>
<br>
But I realize people HATE restrictions. They are already crying about all the ones that are in place and the low server population.<br>
<br>
SO, how about more incentives (sort of like the Sullon Zek XP Bonus):<br>
<br>
- Higher group XP bonuses (to encourage social behavior)<br>
- XP bonuses when all members of a group are same race or maybe same religion (to encourage unity of purpose for roleplaying).<br>
- General XP bonuses to those of evil or good alignments, so that people will take a stand! (Seems like many people are going Neutral for grouping reasons and I hate to see Good/Evil discouraged for game mechanics reasons on an RP server. Of course I'd hate seeing Good and Evil in the same group/guild even more!)<br>
- XP bonus if guilded (again, encourage social behavior)<br>
<br>
Anyway, feel free to think of more &quot;incentives&quot; and I'll probably support them to increase the server population. However, I will not support ANY easing of current &quot;restrictions&quot; on FV.<br>
<br>
Grimwyrd Storm<br>
